Just wanted to say that an easy way to get around the serious audio "delay" is to add about one second of delay via something like VLC. In VLC it's the letter "k" and pump that up to 1000 ms - around there you'll be fine.
Thanks ahiromu, I didn't know that about VLC and it'll make watching this season a lot more enjoyable.

This is an old Torrent but since it still has a healthy number of seeders I wanted to post.  As others have mentioned the audio is very out of sync for 3 episodes.  Below are the audio delay parameters I used to deminish the issue.  Using those values should bring the audio/video sync back to an acceptable level.

The OC [HDTV] - Season 1, Episode 5 - 1290ms
The OC [HDTV] - Season 1, Episode 7 - 1270ms
The OC [HDTV] - Season 1, Episode 6 - 500ms

If you don't know what to do with these values here are 3 approaches:

1.  -(FIX) Realign the Audio Video tracks with VirtualDub and resave the corrected file.
(http://www.tutorialsroom.com/tutorials/av/vdub_adjust_sync.html)

2.  -(VIEW) Play the video file with the modded  release of Media Player Classic (MPC) and adjust the audio delay in the app.
(http://forum.videohelp.com/threads/257022-How-to-fix-audio-synch-problem-in-AVI-file/page5)

3.  -(VIEW) Play the video file with the VLC Player and adjust the audio delay in the app.
(http://filesharingtalk.com/threads/261404-How-to-fix-audio-out-of-sync-in-VLC-Player)
